Engine Overspeed - Fuel to injectors disabled until engine speed falls below the overspeed limit.
High Coolant Temperature (RPM) - Power derate and possible engine shutdown if engine protection shutdown feature is enabled.
Low Coolant Level - Power and/or speed derate and possible engine shutdown if engine protection shutdown feature enabled.
Low Oil Pressure - Power derate and possible engine shutdown if engine protection shutdown feature enabled.
OBD values are not displayed in INSITE for this engine program.
